2500|$|A [...] element, {{and inside}} that, [...] elements, {{each of which}} defines a single {{clickable}} area within the imagemap. These {{are similar to the}} [...] tag defining which URL should be opened for an ordinary web link. A title attribute may be provided, which may be rendered as a tooltip if a desktop user hovers their mouse pointer over the area. For web accessibility reasons, it is often important – and in some cases it may even be a legal or contractual requirement – to provide an alt attribute describing the link that <b>screen</b> <b>reader</b> software can read to, for example, blind users.|$|E
