2500|$|Amazon's upgrade of the {{standard}} Kindle was released on June 22, 2016 in {{both black and white}} colors ($80 ad-supported, $100 no ads). The Kindle 8 features a new rounded design that is [...] shorter, [...] narrower, [...] thinner, and [...] lighter than the previous Kindle 7, and features double the RAM (512MB) of its predecessor. The Kindle 8 is the first Kindle to use Bluetooth that can support VoiceView <b>screen</b> <b>reader</b> software for the seeing impaired. It has the same screen display as its predecessor, a 167 ppi E Ink Pearl touch-screen display, and Amazon claims it has a four-week battery life and can be fully charged within four hours.|$|E
